# 6. マックスを知るために

Akito: I should get to know Max better...?
Honami: Yes, such as what makes him happy or upset... As well as how he moves and reacts to things...
Honami: If you learn those things and develop some trust, I have a feeling that you'll become much more comfortable around him.
Akito: I see...
Akito: (I guess I get what she's saying...)
Akito: (But is learning more about who he is really gonna help me feel less scared...?)
Max: Woof!
Akito: ...
Akito: (No, I have to give it a try...)
Akito: (The reason I said I'd take Ishihara's place in that competition at all is because I could tell Max cares about his partner.)
Akito: (If I can learn more about Max's personality like Mochizuki said, then...)
Akito: Okay... I'll give it a try.
Honami: Wonderful...!
Akito: Still, how exactly am I supposed to get to know Max better...?
Honami: Oh, about that... Why don't we start by watching how he behaves normally?
Honami: We can stand at a bit of a distance. That should be less stressful for you.
Rui: That sounds good. The simple act of observing with interest should give you more than enough information.
Minori: Oh, I know! What if we all...?!
Dogs: Woof! *Bark* Woof.
Honami: No, Shibao, don't tug on your leash!
Minori: They're so excited about making new friends!
Rui: Yes, including Robo-Dog.
Robo-Dog: *Howl*
Akito: ...
Akito: (Who would've guessed the day would come when I'd be dog-watching...?)
Akito: (But...)
Akito: (I feel like I'm not learning much just seeing him walk around like this... Is this enough?)
Rui: How are you feeling, Shinonome?
Akito: Uhh... Okay. We are standing pretty far away.
Akito: But I'm not sure if I'm really learning anything about Max.
Rui: Really? I thought going for a walk together was a wonderful idea.
Akito: Huh...?
Rui: For example, Samo's walking in lockstep with Hanasato, which tells me that he likes receiving attention from her...
Akito: ...
Rui: Shibao has a strong sense of curiosity. So strong that he can't seem to stay away from Robo-Dog.
Akito: Really...?
Rui: Hehe. Shall we put that to the test?
Rui: Robo-Dog, triple Axel!
Robo-Dog: *Howl*
Shibao: !!
Minori: What?! Did Robo-Dog just jump up and twirl around in the air?!
Honami: Oh... Hehe. Shibao can't seem to get enough of him.
Minori: Yeah! He's sniffing him so much!
Rui: See?
Akito: (Wait, why's it able to jump like that...?)
Akito: (Still, it's pretty clear now that each dog has a different personality...)
Rui: Now, what about Max...?
Akito: ...
Akito: (He walks a lot slower than the other dogs...)
Akito: (He's even stopping to look at Ishihara from time to time for some reason...)
Akito: (Is he worrying about his partner's ankle...?)
Child: Whoa! Look at all the doggies!
Akito: Hm?
Mother: Stop! You shouldn't try to touch them without asking. I'm so sorry...
Honami: No, that's okay. Hehe. Do you like dogs?
Child: Yeah! It's really cool how smooth this one's fur is!
Ishihara: Oh, are you talking about Max? Would you like to try petting him?
Child: Really?! Yay! Hehe. I'm gonna pet his head!
Akito: (Hm? His head...?)
Honami: I'd avoid his head or bottom since many dogs don't like being touched there immediately.
Akito: (Uh-oh...)
Akito: Wait, don't go touching his...
Max: ...
Akito: (He's fine with it? No, he looks a little uncomfortable... But he's not doing anything about it...)
Max: *Lick*
Child: H-Haha! Mom, he licked me!
Mother: That's wonderful. Now, you should thank this young man for letting you pet his dog.
Child: Okay! Thanks for letting me pet your dog! Bye bye, doggie!
Mother: Thank you for being so kind.
Akito: He was so calm...
Ishihara: Huh?
Akito: He didn't like being touched on the head, right?
Ishihara: Oh, right. But Max wouldn't kick up a fuss over that.
Ishihara: He also knew that it was a kid who was petting him... He's just a really nice guy!
Akito: Yeah, I could tell...
Akito: (He's been worried sick about his partner's ankle...)
Akito: (And he didn't bark at that kid or anything, even though he was uncomfortable.)
Akito: (He's really just that nice...)
Honami: How do you feel now, Shinonome?
Akito: Hm? Oh, uhh...
Akito: Yeah, I think I have a slightly better idea of what he's like. I'm definitely less scared of him now...
Minori: Really?! Yay! My idea worked!
Honami: Yes, it did! Then, why don't we keep watching Max for a little while longer?
Akito: Okay, but... I don't know how much more I'll get out of just watching him go for a walk...
Honami: Oh, right... Maybe we should have him do a few different things.
Rui: In that case, why don't we try something a little more interesting next...?
